<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by SefaAkajira on 04-19-2001 06:47 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> "On fennin ro it is total chaos when RF spawns ... This is a BIG source to unhappy inhabitants of Norrath. Currently no guilds like each others."

  It is not just Fennin Ro!  The way the epics are designed, and not just the cleric epic, this is the pattern on other servers as well.  On Erollsi Marr the 'uber' guilds are there as soon as servers come back online and "CAMPED" is shouted for all these rare spawns.  Never mind the majority of us on the server who prefer our smaller guilds - even if we can unite to have a reasonable chance at one of these high-level spawns, we can not get there in time.

  Saddest, from talking with other guild leaders, is the slow migration from our guilds to the 'uber' guilds because "the only way I can ever hope to get my epic".  Of course I think we all have those whose loyalty is to the guild and choose to stay, resigned to never being able to have their epics - and that hurts as well.

  I doubt Verant *cares* that what they have created by these poor designs is causing such resentment among their customers.  For every one that cancels their account because of the frustrations caused by the poor design for many quest spawns, another two or three will buy the "Game of the Year".  A revolving door.

   To make the Epics challenging is definitely the objective of an "epic" quest. But to design so that only a small percentage of its customer base can ever complete the quest because they can not hope to get the necessary spawns is simply a disregard for the customer that pays the monthly fees.   I've come to resent supporting financially a "service" that has such a complete disregard for me as its customer -- and yeah, I'd cancel my account and move on --- but the friendships with very REAL people are stronger than my resentment for Verant's poor designs and lack of consideration.

   The problem is easily remedied --
Triggered spawns that are "soul-bound" to the one who triggered the spawn -- so ONLY that person can loot for the first 5 minutes.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
